The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, October 10, 2002 				 Kid-friendly puja
																								With the city gearing up for its biggest festival, Prayasam aims to see how child-friendly the pandals are and, accordingly, has organised a team of seven child judges  Ariunava Hazra, Gaurav Talukdar, Dipa Saha, Nivedita Bhardwaj, Sayan Choudhury, Anurupa Bose and Shibashish Ghosh  of different city schools who will go around the city today, shortlisting pandals that meet their parameters of selection: cleanliness, safety precautions and opportunities for children. This programme has been thus titled, Khadims Nojor Kara Aamader Para Shishubondhu Sharod Purashkar, supervised by UNICEF. The theme is we shall try to remain in the pink of health during the glowing days of the pujas. Pujo Porikroma is an affirmation of Prayasams policy of child participation in its various programmes. Children from all walks of life will be wearing the same T-shirt that will bring about a sense of togetherness. Tomorrow the young judges will lead a medley of 200 children from Rishi Aurobindo Colony, Ultadanga. On the day of Ashtami, the child judges will declare the award winners and on Nabami, the best pandal and puja committee will be announced. 																								When: October 10, 11, 13 and 14
